Templates are Beanstalk's powerful string-building form.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    name = "Ada"

    greeting = [:
        Hello, [name]
    ]
]

Square brackets create the template.

The colon separates its head from its body.

A nested template inserts a value from the surrounding scope.

Templates can build plain text, Markdown, HTML, CSS or another string-based
format. They may be finished during compilation or built at runtime.
